text: The 2020 United States presidential election in New Jersey was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Former Vice President Joe Biden and his running mate U.S. SenatorKamala Harris had won 14 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in New Jersey
title: 2020 United States presidential election in New Jersey
